  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Advanced control of neutral beam injected power in DIII-D</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-27</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• A new control scheme for neutral beam operation has been implemented on DIII-D. • The new control allows for beam voltage to be changed in real time during a beam shot. • This variable beam energy (VBE) mode is controlled by the DIII-D plasma control system (PCS). • Additional control changes as part of the VBE operation have allowed for beam perveance sweeps in a single shot. • The new control maintains beamline safety and tracks energy efficiency.</subfield>
